1a0e139c-9d19-48f2-b4fe-6c168a620d27.do_description: To make the output, you have to...go up from the red add one more green square as you go up.  If you start with 2 red squares the next would be 3 green.  Then go down from the red and use blue square.  The number should be one less than the red to start
1a0e139c-9d19-48f2-b4fe-6c168a620d27.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same as the input
1a0e139c-9d19-48f2-b4fe-6c168a620d27.see_description: In the input, you should see...a pattern of green, red and blue squares

ab04621a-32ed-40b0-bf89-209661b559ad.do_description: To make the output, you have to...copy your red input boxes to the output grid. Make an exact same line (as red) in green, but also add  1 green box. Repeat moving up until your top portion is colored in green with -1 box moving downward. Go to the box(es) just BELOW your red line. Make a new line (or box) in blue, but -1 less blue box than the number of red box(es). Repeat this in blue until you only have ONE black box (row) left on the bottom. In the end  you will have green, red, blue and it will zig-zag getting smaller as you go down. Be sure to leave the very bottom row all black.
ab04621a-32ed-40b0-bf89-209661b559ad.grid_description: The output grid size...exactly the same as the input grid.
ab04621a-32ed-40b0-bf89-209661b559ad.see_description: In the input, you should see...a black grid with a small horizontal line in red.

b42f7601-1f42-4288-8c7d-85ba31f1e6f4.do_description: To make the output, you have to...place the horizontal bar in the exact position in the output. Then add 1 to the number of orange squares and fill in that number of squares directly above the orange bar, but in GREEN, beginning with the leftmost square. Then add another 1, and fill in that number of squares in another green horizontal bar right above. Continue doing that all the way to the top. Then subtract the number of the original orange squares by 1, then draw under the orange bar the new number of squares in BLUE, also beginning with the leftmost square. Repeat until the number of blue squares is 1. Draw that, then you are done.
b42f7601-1f42-4288-8c7d-85ba31f1e6f4.grid_description: The output grid size...is the same.
b42f7601-1f42-4288-8c7d-85ba31f1e6f4.see_description: In the input, you should see...horizontal bar of orange squares, either 2, 3, or 4 squares.
